  "why": "While the paper uses a dual-model design (a resistant and a vulnerable model) as an agreement-mining oracle during fuzzing, it does not demonstrate or evaluate whether fault-inducing inputs discovered on one model transfer to separate, unseen target models. All experiments report robustness improvements by fine-tuning the same (pre-adversarially trained) models with test cases generated by TWINFUZZ, and the evaluations focus on cross-attack and cross-domain generalization rather than cross-model transfer. Thus the paper does not provide post-hoc cross-model transferability evidence nor explicit design choices to discover transferable attacks across independently trained target models.",
